headlines.description: — Manchester City passed a huge test of its Premier League title credentials by beating Newcastle 2-0 on Saturday as a couple of big calls by Pep Guardiola paid off in a match between the wealthiest teams in English soccer.
headlines.shortLinkText: Man City beats Newcastle 2-0, stays in touch with Arsenal

headlines.description: — Conceding a goal after just nine seconds and going 2-0 down in the second half wasn’t enough to derail Arsenal’s title bid in the English Premier League.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nelson nets winner in Arsenal comeback against Bournemouth

headlines.description: — A first-half own goal handed Aston Villa a 1-0 victory and kept Crystal Palace winless in 2023 in the English Premier League on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Aston Villa wins on own goal, Crystal Palace winless in 2023

events.name: West Ham United at Brighton & Hove Albion

headlines.description: Brighton beat a woeful West Ham United 4-0 at home in the Premier League on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Brighton ease to 4-0 rout over woeful West Ham

headlines.description: A leaping header from Wesley Fofana earned Chelsea a Premier League win against struggling Leeds United on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Chelsea edge Leeds to ease pressure on Potter

headlines.description: Adama Traore was on target as a spirited Wolves stunned a wasteful Tottenham 1-0 at the Molineux Stadium in the Premier League on Saturday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Traore on target as Wolves stun wasteful Spurs

headlines.description: Carlos Alcaraz grabbed the only goal as Southampton beat Leicester City 1-0 at St Mary's Stadium on Saturday to move off the bottom of the table.
headlines.shortLinkText: Southampton edge Leicester to move off bottom
